#, no-wrap
msgid "Zero-config setup in development mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/datasource.adoc:44
msgid "Quarkus simplifies database configuration by offering the Dev Services feature, enabling zero-config database setup for testing or running in development (dev) mode.  In dev mode, the suggested approach is to use DevServices and let Quarkus handle the database for you, whereas for production mode, you provide explicit database configuration details pointing to a database managed outside of Quarkus."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: upstream/_versions/main/guides/datasource.adoc:47
msgid "To use Dev Services, add the appropriate driver extension, such as `jdbc-postgresql`, for your desired database type to the `pom.xml` file.  In dev mode, if you do not provide any explicit database connection details, Quarkus automatically handles the database setup and provides the wiring between the application and the database."
